It should be noted that these dimensions occur with the 1.4 engine version, as the luggage capacity of the Honda Jazz 1.2 is 379 litres.
Another improvement, in addition to the external features - such as the rear LED lights or the possibility of equipment with a glass panoramic roof - is easier to access the rear seats.
The door leading to the second row of seats allows the angle of opening of 80 degrees, compared to the first Jazz.
For the second-generation Honda Jazz, the engines are new.
Initially, this small model will be offered with two 1.2 and 1.4-litre petrol engines.
Both engines use i-VTEC technology that allows lower consumption, lower carbon dioxide emissions and deliver an excellent fuel system improvement at the same time as high torque in full engine speed.
The first 1.2-litre engine has a power output of 90 hp at 6,000 rpm with a maximum torque of 114 Nm at 4,900 rpm.
This engine - which had a 2.3-litre consumption of the previous generation of the Jazz 780 - has a consumption of 5.3 litres and an emission of 125 grams of CO2.
Compared to the previous engine, which reached 83 horsepower for the previous generation, the current one will reach 100.
The 100-horsepower Honda Jazz 1.4 has a combined consumption of 5.4 litres and an emission of 128 grams of CO2.
